<html><head><title>Classes Available for Drakkin</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Classes Available for Drakkin</h3><p>An interesting thing about the newest race for EQ, the Drakkin, is that they have a color associated with their class choice and an innate resistance that goes along with the color of their hair and scale markings.  Obviously, this is all subject to change when the expansion goes live, but currently on the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/expansions/theserpentsspine/">official website</a> the classes available for a Drakkin to specialize in are:<br><br>Red Drakkin, Masters of War and Fire, have an innate fire resistance:<br>Warrior, Shadowknight, Cleric, Rogue, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage, Necromancer<br><br>Black Drakkin, Masters of Shadows and Secrets, have innate disease resistance:<br>Warrior, Shadowknight, Cleric, Rogue, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage, Necromancer<br><br>Green Drakkin,  Masters of Nature and Creation, and have an innate resistance to poison:<br>Warrior, Ranger, Monk, Cleric, Druid, Rogue, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage<br><br>Blue Drakkin, Masters of Serenity and Peace, have an innate resistance to magic:<br>Warrior, Ranger, Monk, Cleric, Rogue, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage<br><br>Silver Drakkin, Masters of Wisdom and Spirituality, have an innate resitance to cold:<br>Warrior, Paladin, Monk, Cleric, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage<br><br>Gold Drakkin, Masters of Enlightenment and Knowledge, have a slight resistance to all forms of magic:<br>Warrior, Paladin, Monk, Cleric, Bard, Enchanter, Wizard, Mage<br></div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Tuesday, 22 August, 2006<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=20488">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=20488</a><br>Printed On: Wed Oct 18 1:03:42 PDT 2006<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>